    <abstract id="Abs3" abstract-type="LongSummary">
      <title>A window on salmonid genome evolution</title>
      <p>William Davidson and colleagues report sequencing and assembly of the Atlantic salmon genome, which they demonstrate as a useful reference to also improve the genome assembly of other salmanoids. Their analyses provide insights into duplicate retention patterns across two rounds of whole-genome duplication that have occurred in this lineage.</p>
